  body
    div(class="container")
      h3 API Project: #{title}
      div(class="row")
        div(class="ten columns")
          p The api gets passed a string as a parameter, and checks to see whether that string is a valid URL, eg https://www.google.com
          p If it is, it returns both the original URL and a shortened version of that URL. Which when visited redirects to the original URL/link.
          p If it is passed an invalid URL that doesn't follow the valid http://www.example.com format, the JSON response will contain an error instead

          h4 Usage
          p !{' '}
            a(href="/api/shorten/https://freecodecamp.org", target="_blank") #{projectUrl}/api/shorten/https://freecodecamp.org
            br
            pre
              code
                |
                |   {
                |     original_url: "https://freecodecamp.org",
                |     short_url: "#{projectUrl}/xxxxx"
                |   }
                |
                |
